    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Regarding your example, wouldn't this be a simpler way to solve the issue?\n\n``` javascript\ninstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\n  container: '#myfacet',\n  facetName: 'myfacet',\n  template: '{{ value }}',\n  transformData: function (refinement) {\n    return { value: '$' + refinement.value };\n  }\n});\n```\n\nI feel the `transformData` is about transforming the data we got from the widget before passing it to the template. But not go too deep inside what helpers the Mustache render method has available. This should just be a _take object as input, returns object as output_ IMHO.\n",
